{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599283","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599283"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:51:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:51:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15539"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15539","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15539"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.06,0.33,0.09,0.42]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8230"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70302"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8230","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8230"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15539"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55766"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6965"},{"type":"tags","id":"6976"},{"type":"tags","id":"8745"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19900"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19903"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70302","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70302"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe image shows a cross-sectional view of the pancreas and its ductal system.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures is labelled at point (7)?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Common bile duct","Main pancreatic duct","Major duodenal papilla","Minor duodenal papilla","Hepatopancreatic ampulla"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe image shows the hepatopancreaticobiliary system. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ecommon bile duct\u003C/strong\u003E joins the main pancreatic duct to form the hepatopancreatic ampulla or ampulla of Vater. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ehepatopancreatic ampulla\u003C/strong\u003E serves as a reservoir for pancreatic juice and bile. The \u003Cstrong\u003Emain pancreatic duct\u003C/strong\u003E (duct of Wirsung) is the primary drainage system of the pancreas. The \u003Cstrong\u003Emajor duodenal papilla\u003C/strong\u003E is the opening of the hepatopancreatic ampulla to the duodenum. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eminor duodenal papilla\u003C/strong\u003E is where the accessory pancreatic duct opens into the duodenum.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The accessory pancreatic duct (duct of Santorini) drains the superior part of the head of the pancreas into the minor duodenal papilla.","The main pancreatic duct joins with the common bile duct to form the hepatopancreatic ampulla (ampulla of Vater) which opens at the major duodenal papilla."],"references":["\u0022Biliary system multilingual.\u0022 by Jmarchn is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license. https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Biliary_system_multilingual.svg","Nightingale, J. M. (2012). Applied anatomy and physiology of the gastrointestinal tract (GIT). Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book: Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book, 45.","Podolsky, D. K., Camilleri, M., Fitz, J. G., Kalloo, A. N., Shanahan, F., \u0026 Wang, T. C. (Eds.). (2015). Yamada\u0027s textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Matli VVK, Wellman G, Jaganmohan S, Koticha K. Ampullary and Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumors: A Series of Cases and Review of the Literature. Cureus. 2022 Jan 27;14(1):e21657. do